1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,600
Hey everyone, welcome. You know, there's
this one English puzzle that trips up
everyone when they're learning.

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:10,240
Even little kids in America. It's all
about comparing things and today we're
going to crack the code together.

3
00:00:10,240 --> 00:00:16,000
You ready? All right, let's get right to
it. Take a look at this sentence on your
screen.

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:21,920
Health is importanter than money. Does
that sound a little weird to you?

5
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:28,320
Like something's just not right?
Importanter. That word definitely feels
like an imposter.

6
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:32,480
So, what is going on here? And you know
what?

7
00:00:32,480 --> 00:00:35,560
Your brain is totally right. That word is
wrong.

8
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:38,160
And that brings us to the big mystery for
today.

9
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:41,480
When do we use ER and when do we need
something else?

10
00:00:41,480 --> 00:00:42,880
Let's figure this out.

11
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:47,360
Okay, so this slide right here gives us
our first major clue.

12
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:49,200
Over on the left, you've got your short
words.

13
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:52,000
You know these guys, tall, big, wide.

14
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:57,640
You just add ER, taller, bigger, easy
peasy, but then look at the right.

15
00:00:57,640 --> 00:01:00,040
These are the final bosses of the video
game, right?

16
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:03,200
Important, difficult, beautiful.

17
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:06,040
Trying to add ER to them just doesn't
work.

18
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:11,160
So we need a new superpower. And that
superpower, well, the key,

19
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:13,680
the secret password to solving this whole
thing,

20
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:18,680
it's all about how long the word is. Yep,
for these longer words,

21
00:01:18,680 --> 00:01:21,780
trying to add ER is just not gonna happen.

22
00:01:21,780 --> 00:01:25,040
But don't worry, we've got something way,
way cooler.

23
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:28,080
It's like a secret magic spell. And here
they are.

24
00:01:28,080 --> 00:01:33,240
The magic words are more and most. That's
it, that's the secret.

25
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:36,200
You don't change the long word at all.
Nope, don't touch it.

26
00:01:36,200 --> 00:01:39,640
You just put one of these special words
right in front of it.

27
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:43,480
How simple is that? So how do we use these
magic words?

28
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:44,980
Well, it's super easy.

29
00:01:44,980 --> 00:01:47,280
If you're comparing just two things, you
use more.

30
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:50,400
So remember our weird sentence from the
beginning? We can fix it now.

31
00:01:50,400 --> 00:01:53,960
Health is more important than money. See,
perfect.

32
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:56,320
And what if you're comparing like three or
more things

33
00:01:56,320 --> 00:02:00,560
and one is the absolute number one, then
you use the most.

34
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:05,200
Health is the most important thing. Boom,
mystery solved.

35
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:08,040
Okay, let's practice with some real life
examples.

36
00:02:08,040 --> 00:02:10,560
I think we can all agree on this one,
right?

37
00:02:10,560 --> 00:02:12,360
For many students, video games

38
