This action movie is more exciting than
that drama.

41
00:02:20,640 --> 00:02:21,920
And when we talk about music,

42
00:02:21,920 --> 00:02:25,160
we always wanna know who is the most
famous singer

43
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:29,000
in America right now. See how it works?
It's everywhere.

44
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:33,680
Just look at this table. Once you see the
pattern, you can't unsee it.

45
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:37,240
Beautiful, more beautiful, the most
beautiful.

46
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,880
Difficult, more difficult, the most
difficult.

47
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:43,320
The main word stays exactly the same.

48
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:46,840
It's a fantastic, super reliable rule.

49
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:49,240
All right, you've totally mastered the
main level,

50
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:52,120
so are you ready for a secret bonus round?

51
00:02:52,120 --> 00:02:57,360
Let's talk about a special group of words,
the LI words.

52
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:58,360
And guess what?

53
00:02:58,360 --> 00:03:01,400
The best news is, you don't really have to
learn a new rule.

54
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:05,680
For most words that end in LI, you just
use our magic words again.

55
00:03:05,680 --> 00:03:08,880
Like Bob spoke more slowly than Jane.

56
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:13,840
Or maybe your teacher in a quiet library
might say, please speak more quietly.

57
00:03:13,840 --> 00:03:14,840
It just works.

58
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:21,440
But wait, just when you think it's all
perfectly simple, English loves to throw
in a surprise,

59
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:26,640
right? Always one little exception that
just loves to break the rules.

60
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:29,340
And that rule breaker is the word early.

61
00:03:29,340 --> 00:03:33,020
So even though it ends in L-Y, it pretends
it's a short word.

62
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:36,000
We don't say more early, no way.

63
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:38,920
We say Jennifer got up earlier than Emily.

64
00:03:38,920 --> 00:03:42,320
And the person who gets up first gets up
the earliest.

65
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:45,520
This is a big one to remember, so lock it
in your brain.

66
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:49,800
Okay team, you've collected all the clues,
you've solved the puzzles, let's do a
quick

67
